{
  "texts": [
    "Following the input layer is the convolutional layer.",
    "During this phase, the layer traverses the image in small sections, referred to as filters or kernels, to construct a feature map.",
    "Feature maps enable CNN to recognize fundamental shapes or patterns, including lines or textures.",
    "Subsequently, the activation function, typically the ReLU (Rectified Linear Unit), is applied.",
    "This function enhances the CNN's learning capabilities by nullifying any negative pixel values, thereby increasing the effectiveness of the CNN in identifying complex patterns."
  ]
}